      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2008 Porsche Cayman S, a mid-engine masterpiece featuring the 3.4L M97.21 flat-six powerplant. This unit delivers 295 hp with a linear torque curve, sent to the rear wheels via a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis geometry remains precise, benefiting from a low center of gravity and optimized polar moment of inertia. The braking system utilizes four-piston monobloc calipers and ventilated, cross-drilled rotors for superior heat dissipation. This example has been meticulously maintained with a focus on mechanical longevity, including a recent cooling system overhaul and a proactive AOS replacement. The hydraulic steering rack provides the communicative feedback desired by purists, while the suspension bushings and dampers remain firm, ensuring the car tracks true through high-load cornering. A mechanically sound, driver-focused specimen ready for the apex.",
